definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  2,6-dihydroxypseudooxynicotine + H2O -eq- 2,6-dihydroxypyridine + 4-methylaminobutyrate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  1,1-dichloroethane + 2 H+ + 2 e- -eq- chloroethane + HCl.
Catalysis of the reaction -  phenylboronic acid + O2 + 2 H+ + 2 e- -eq- phenol + B(OH)3.
Catalysis of the reaction -  o-hydroxylaminobenzoate -eq- 3-hydroxyanthranilate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  malonate semialdehyde + H+ -eq- acetaldehyde + CO2.
Catalysis of the reaction -  perillyl-CoA + H2O -eq- 2-hydroxy-4-isopropenylcyclohexane-1-carboxyl-CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  diphenyl ether + O2 -eq- 2,3-dihydroxydiphenyl ether.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2,3-dihydroxydiphenyl ether + O2 + H2O -eq- 2-hydroxymuconate + phenol.
Catalysis of the reaction -  diphenyl ether + NADH + O2 + H+ -eq- phenol + catechol + NAD+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3-nitrophenol + 2 NADH + 2 H+ -eq- 3-hydroxyaminophenol + 2 NAD+ + H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  aminohydroquinone + 2 e- + 2 H+ + 1|2 O2 -eq- 1,2,4-benzenetriol + NH3.
A histone deacetylase complex that is involved in transcriptional regulation. In S. cerevisiae, this complex consists of Set3p, Snt1p, Hos4p, Sif2p, Cpr1p, Hos2p, and Hst1p.

A protein complex that contains a protein kinase (Sid2 in S. pombe) and its regulatory subunit (Mob1). The Sid2p-Mob1p kinase complex is a component of the septation initiation network in fission yeast (called the mitotic exit network in S. cerevisiae) and is required for cytokinesis. The analogous complex in S. cerevisiae is called Dbf2p-Mob1p complex.
A protein complex involved that contains proteins known in Schizosaccharomyces as Swi5 monomers and Swi2, and is involved in mating type switching.

A protein complex that contains the precursor form of NF-kappaB (p105), the NF-kappaB inhibitor ABIN-2, and the kinase TPL-2 (MAP3K8) -  the complex stabilizes TPL-2 and is involved in signaling in lipopolysaccharide (LPS)-stimulated macrophages.
A protein complex that contains the homeodomain proteins PDX1, PBX1b and MRG1 (MEIS2) and is involved in the transcriptional regulation of pancreatic acinar cell-specific genes.
Catalysis of the removal of one or more acetyl groups from a protein, requiring NAD.
A protein complex that contains CREB and FHL2, and is involved in transcriptional regulation.
A protein complex that contains CREB and FHL3, and is involved in transcriptional regulation.

Any large protein complex that contains Ecsit and NDUFAF1, is located in the mitochondrion, and is involved in the assembly of complex I of the oxidative phosphorylation system. In mammalian cells, three complexes of approximately 500, 600, and 850 kDa containing the 45 kDa isoform of Ecsit and NDUFAF1 have been observed.
Assists in the delivery of iron ions to target proteins or compartments.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with one or more specific sites on an immunoglobulin receptor molecule.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with one or more specific sites on the Fc-gamma receptor I complex. The complex functions primarily as an activating receptor for IgG.
A cohesin complex that mediates sister chromatid cohesion in the nucleus during mitosis -  has a subunit composition distinct from that of the meiotic cohesin complex.
A cohesin complex that mediates sister chromatid cohesion in the nucleus during meiosis -  has a subunit composition distinct from that of the meiotic cohesin complex.

A region of the nuclear envelope to which a microtubule organizing center (MTOC) attaches -  protein complexes embedded in the nuclear envelope mediate direct or indirect linkages between the microtubule cytoskeleton and the nuclear envelope.

A protein complex that spans the nuclear outer and inner membranes, thereby linking the major cytoplasmic cytoskeleton elements to the nuclear lumen -  the complex is conserved in eukaryotes and contains proteins with SUN and KASH domains.
A protein complex that consist of complement components C5b6 and C7 stably inserted in a cell membrane. Formation of the SC5b-7 complex is the first phase of membrane attack complex assembly.

A protein complex that consists of a GTPase activator protein (GAP) for Ras and three Src family protein tyrosine kinases, Fyn, Lyn and Yes. The complex is involved in signaling upon platelet activation.
A protein complex that comprises one integrin alphav subunit, one integrin beta5 subunit, and vitronectin.

An oligosaccharyltransferase (OST) complex that contains at least seven polypeptides and is the major OST complex in mammalian cells. Of the three forms of mammalian OST complex identified, the OSTI complex has the weakest affinity for ribosomes.

An oligosaccharyltransferase (OST) complex that contains the seven polypeptides found in OST complex I, plus heterotrimeric Sec61alpha-beta-gamma. Of the three forms of mammalian OST complexes identified, the OSTII complex has intermediate affinity for ribosomes.

An oligosaccharyltransferase (OST) complex that contains the seven polypeptides found in OST complex I, plus heterotrimeric Sec61alpha-beta-gamma and the tetrameric TRAP complex. Of the three forms of mammalian OST complexes identified, the OSTIII complex has the strongest affinity for ribosomes.

The most apical region of the lateral plasma membrane of an invertebrate epithelial cell. The subapical complex lies above the zonula adherens and the septate junction, and is comparable to the position of the tight junction of vertebrate cells.

Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + a phosphatidylinositol -eq- ADP + a phosphatidylinositol 3-phosphate. This reaction is the addition of a phosphate group to phosphatidylinositol or one of its phosphorylated derivatives at the 3' position of the inositol ring.
Catalysis of the reaction -  1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 4-phosphate + ATP -eq- 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 3,4-bisphosphate + ADP + 2 H(+).
The terminal region of a polytene chromosome.
Combining with the peptide myosuppressin to initiate a change in cell activity.

Modulates the activity of any of the phosphatidylinositol 3-kinases (PI3Ks). Regulatory subunits can link a PI3K catalytic subunit to upstream signaling events and help position the catalytic subunits close to their lipid substrates.

A phosphatidylinositol 3-kinase complex that contains a catalytic class III phosphoinositide 3-kinase (PI3K) subunit bound to a regulatory (adaptor) subunit. Additional adaptor proteins may be present. Class III PI3Ks have a substrate specificity restricted to phosphatidylinositol (PI).
Modulates the activity of histone deacetylase.
Modulates the activity of histone acetyltransferase.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with the enzyme histone acetyltransferase.
Catalysis of the transfer of a methyl group to juvenile hormone acid.
A protein complex that facilitates the assembly of nucleosomes on to newly synthesized DNA. In Drosophila, the complex comprises ASF1 and histones H3 and H4.
A SWI|SNF-type complex that contains the ATPase product of the Drosophila brahma gene, or an ortholog thereof.

A class of nuclear body measuring 20-25 nm in diameter and distributed throughout the interchromatin space, linked together by thin fibrils. They are believed to be storage centers for various snRNAs, snRNPs, serine|arginine-rich proteins and RNA polymerase II. A typical mammalian cell contains 25-50 clusters of interchromatin granules. Interchromatin granule clusters do not contain the heterogeneous nuclear RNA-binding proteins (hnRNPs).

A nucleoplasmic speckle distributed in the interchromatin space of cells in close proximity to chromatin. Omega speckles are distinct from interchromatin granules and contain heterogeneous nuclear RNA-binding proteins (hnRNPs).

Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a histone protein in which a residue has been modified by methylation. Histones are any of a group of water-soluble proteins found in association with the DNA of plant and animal chromosomes.

A complex containing both protein and micro-RNA (miRNA) molecules. miRNAs are approximately 22 nucleotide noncoding RNAs derived from endogenous genes -  they are processed from the stem of a longer hairpin like structure termed a pre-miRNA.
